      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "When the stakes involve existential risk, the argument for prioritizing safety becomes logically overwhelming. Advocates for strong regulation contend that the potential cost of extinction dwarfs any short-term economic gains from unchecked innovation. From this perspective, a pause or strict control is a rational risk-mitigation strategy when facing a potential irreversible catastrophe. Therefore, existential safety must logically outweigh the imperative for speed or market dominance.",
